adjectives.description: indeprivable (comparative more indeprivable, superlative most indeprivable)

entries.meaning: (now rare) That one cannot be deprived of; inalienable.
examples: [P]erhaps Birth may be really the sole indeprivable Good, I can think of nothing else which one cannot lose by Folly or by Accident—Virtue excluded, and that is a Quality that Italians do not trouble themselves to think of.
